  "body": "Currently in Solidity, if there are multiple require/assert statements. You would not know which require/assert statement caused the exception. It would be super useful if the require/assert statements take into a message as an argument.\r\n\r\nfor example something similar to this.\r\n`require(a>5, \"Error Message: Caused by a>5\");`\r\n   or\r\n`assert(a>5, \"Error message: Caused by a>5\");`\r\n",
